G2420.strongs_def: sacredness, i.e. (by implication) the priestly office

G3142.strongs_def: something evidential, i.e. (genitive case) evidence given or (specially), the Decalogue (in the sacred Tabernacle)
G3142.derivation: neuter of a presumed derivative of G3144 (μάρτυς);

G4438.strongs_def: to box (with the fist), i.e. contend (as a boxer) at the games (figuratively)
G4438.derivation: from a derivative of the same as G4435 (πυγμή);

G1025.strongs_def: an infant (properly, unborn) literally or figuratively

G3931.derivation: from a compound of G3844 (παρά) and a derivative of G58 (ἀγορά) (meaning to harangue an assembly);

G5278.kjv_def: abide, endure, (take) patient(-ly), suffer, tarry behind

G857.derivation: from a compound of G1 (Α) (as a negative particle) and G5339 (φείδομαι);

G5368.strongs_def: to be a friend to (fond of (an individual or an object)), i.e. have affection for (denoting personal attachment, as a matter of sentiment or feeling; while G25 (ἀγαπάω) is wider, embracing especially the judgment and the deliberate assent of the will as a matter of principle, duty and propriety: the two thus stand related very much as G2309 (θέλω) and G1014 (βούλομαι), or as G2372 (θυμός) and G3563 (νοῦς) respectively; the former being chiefly of the heart and the latter of the head); specially, to kiss (as a mark of tenderness)

G2265.derivation: plural of a derivative of G2264 (Ἡρώδης);

G3880.strongs_def: to receive near, i.e. associate with oneself (in any familiar or intimate act or relation); by analogy, to assume an office; figuratively, to learn

G1455.derivation: from G1722 (ἐν) and a derivative of G2524 (καθίημι);
G1455.strongs_def: subinduced, i.e. surreptitiously suborned as a lier-in-wait

G3808.derivation: neuter of a presumed derivative of G3816 (παῖς);

G5192.strongs_def: the "hyacinth" or "jacinth", i.e. some gem of a deep blue color, probably the zirkon

G2232.strongs_def: a leader, i.e. chief person (or figuratively, place) of a province

G1637.derivation: neuter of the same as G1636 (ἐλαία);

G169.derivation: from G1 (Α) (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of G2508 (καθαίρω) (meaning cleansed);

G5104.strongs_def: an enclitic particle of asseveration by way of contrast; in sooth
G5104.derivation: probably for the dative case of G3588 (ὁ);
G5104.kjv_def: (used only with other particles in the comparative, as G2544 (καίτοιγε), G3305 (μέντοι), G5105 (τοιγαροῦν), G5106 (τοίνυν), etc

G1295.kjv_def: bring safe, escape (safe), heal, make perfectly whole, save
G1295.strongs_def: to save thoroughly, i.e. (by implication or analogy) to cure, preserve, rescue, etc.

G473.strongs_def: opposite, i.e. instead or because of (rarely in addition to)

G418.derivation: from G1 (Α) (as a negative particle) and a derivative of the same as G1735 (ἐνδέχεται);

G3144.strongs_def: a witness (literally (judicially) or figuratively (genitive case)); by analogy, a "martyr"

G4889.strongs_def: a co-slave, i.e. servitor or ministrant of the same master (human or divine)

G4292.derivation: middle voice from G4253 (πρό) and G2564 (καλέω);
G4292.strongs_def: to call forth to oneself (challenge), i.e. (by implication) to irritate

G2903.derivation: superlative of a derivative of G2904 (κράτος);

G4342.kjv_def: attend (give self) continually (upon), continue (in, instant in, with), wait on (continually)
G4342.strongs_def: to be earnest towards, i.e. (to a thing) to persevere, be constantly diligent, or (in a place) to attend assiduously all the exercises, or (to a person) to adhere closely to (as a servitor)

G2810.derivation: probably contracted from (compound of G2811 (κλέος) and G3962 (πατήρ));

G4235.derivation: a form of G4239 (πραΰς), used in certain parts;

G897.strongs_def: Babylon, the capitol of Chaldæa (literally or figuratively (as a type of tyranny))

G4203.strongs_def: to act the harlot, i.e. (literally) indulge unlawful lust (of either sex), or (figuratively) practise idolatry

G4629.strongs_def: perhaps akin to the base of G4649 (σκοπός) through the idea of noticeableness); clothing

G2773.strongs_def: a handler of coins, i.e. money-broker
